<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-01T18:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-01T18:16:00-05:00" n="6" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d6">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 871.6131/1</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Roumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-02T01:00:00+01:44">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 2, 1916, 1 a. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 3, 1.30 p.
                                m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>220. As a result of recent Entente purchase of 80,000 cars gram, since
                            confirmed to be wheat, the Central empires threatened Roumania and there
                            was a danger that the present ministry would be changed and a
                            Germanophile ministry with Marghiloman at head placed in power. To avert
                            this the present ministry conferred with and sold Central powers 100,000
                            cars of different kinds of grain. Financial arrangements not yet
                            concluded.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_VCJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vopicka</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>